<|startoftext|>Dish: baked potato crescent
Directions: preheat oven to 375
spray the 9x13 pan with non-stick spray
roll out the pastry , about 7-inches thick
in a large skillet fry the potatoes with 1 tbl of the butter
in a 2 1 / 2 quart plastic bag with the flour , onion , nutmeg , basil , parmesan cheese , garlic , salt and pepper
drop the potato mixture into the pan
roll up the pastry and seal the seams to the crescent seal
place in hot oven and roast for approximately 1 1 / 2 hours , until golden brown and crisp
about 15 minutes longer
remove from oven and cool
meanwhile heat the oil in a small saut pan
crack the eggs into the pan with the egg whites , cooking over medium heat for about 2 minutes to set the whites
pour the butter mixture over the eggs and add the salt and pepper , as desired
place the crescent seal in the bottom of the casserole dish
cover with a foil-lined plastic cover and freeze for several hours
to serve place a slice of bacon on top of one crescent and place another on the top
place potatoes on a platter and arrange the crescent cover
place crescent seam side up
i let it sit on the platter for 30 minutes and then uncovered until the last 30 minutes of baking time
to assemble: remove the pan from the oven and place the crescent on the counter top
remove the crescent from the tray and then place the crescent seam sides down until the casserole is ready'<|endoftext|>
